<TEXT>
authorities shut down a makeshift daycare 
center a bus company was running for its employees in a 
strippeddown bus 
they took the seats out and threw some carpeting down and they 
were in business said groton building official mark w tebbets 
inspectors from state and local fire zoning health and building 
departments who arrived thursday afternoon found three children 
being cared for in the bus which was parked near fuel tanks and a 
trash bin at a bus depot 
we cringe when the tanks are 200 feet away said wesley bell 
the daycare licensing supervisor for the state department of health 
services 
eastern bus lines inc opened the center tuesday owner george 
negro said he hired a baby sitter for children of drivers because a 
new board of education policy prohibits parents from taking their 
preschoolers with them when they drive their routes 
the kids enjoy it so do the parents negro said i hate to 
see anybody foul it up for the parents for myself and for the 
children 
