<TEXT>
the somali army deliberately killed at least 
5000 unarmed civilians in the 10 months preceding last march 
according to a report given to the state department 
the report said the army killed 500 men of the isaak clan most 
of whom died with their throats cut and buried them in a mass 
grave according to an account of the report published saturday by 
the new york times in a dispatch from nairobi kenya 
a us official speaking to the associated press on condition of 
anonymity said the report prepared by robert gersony an outside 
consultant to the state department placed the overall death toll in 
somalia between 5000 and 10000 although it estimated that the 
number probably is closer to the lower end of that range 
the somali government has denied the killings the times reported 
the somali government has repeatedly been accused of human rights 
abuses including one incident this summer in which 46 men were 
reported to have been summarily executed by the army after moslem 
rioting that left 400 people dead 
the human rights group africa watch and other independent sources 
said the people were killed after somali soldiers started shooting 
at houses in mogadishu the nations capital 
gersonys report was based on more than 250 interviews with 
somali refugees the times reported 
the united states recently suspended 25 million in military aid 
and 21 million in econimic aid to somalia to express objection to 
that governments human rights abuses the times said 
</TEXT>
