in the armistice talks with un forces lee served as the deputy 
north korean delegate he later replaced gen nam il as the chief 
communist negotiator in the talks the fighting ended july 27 1953 
but the two countries are still technically at war 
lee defected to the soviet union after serving as north koreas 
ambassador to moscow from 1957 to 1960 he said his defection was to 
avoid kim il sungs mass purge of political enemies 
lees trip to seoul reflects warming relations between south 
korea and the soviet union the countries have no diplomatic 
relations but have expanded nonpolitical contacts significantly in 
recent years they exchanged trade offices early this year 
